                    "company": "Alter Ratio",
                    "description": "2023 marks the 100th birthday of Gy\u00f6rgy Ligeti, a musical avant-garde classic.\nHis most famous vocal work, Lux Aeterna, represents the fusion of new and old in European musical culture.\n\nThe Ukrainian vocal ensemble Alter Ratio will be performing Lux Aeterna in Germany, Switzerland and hopefully also in the Ukraine. Most of the members of Alter Ratio have been living in Germany since the beginning of the war that Russia started against Ukraine. They want to perform this classic piece with some changes. The ensemble consists of 12 singers, Ligeti's work requires 16. The 4 missing voices are \"sung\" by electronics, symbolising that every fourth artist is a victim of this war and has seen the eternal light.\n\nThe text of Lux Aeterna is taken from the Roman Catholic Requiem:\n\n\"May eternal light shine upon them,\nO Lord, with your saints in eternity, for you are merciful. Grant them eternal rest,\nO Lord, and may eternal light shine upon them\".\n\nI have had a long creative relationship with Alter Ratio. In 2016 I wrote for them \"Marian Antiphons\" for 12 voices a cappella, and they are also the first performers of \"Blessing\" for 8 voices. This year I am composing a new piece for ensemble - \"Lullaby of Lullabies\" for vocals with electronics.\n\nThis new work is both an homage to the classic and a continuation of the musical dialogue on an important theme - the culture of memory and the commemoration of the dead.\n\nThe premiere will take place on 17 November at the Klangwerkstatt Berlin 2023, Festival fu\u0308r neue Musik met live-recording by Deutschlandradio Startseite.",
                    "title": "\"Lullaby of Lullabies\" for vocal ensemble with electronics",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
